  "safetyRules": [
    "Ethereum chain ID is pinned to 1 and represented as eip155:1.",
    "No hidden private-key handling, wallet switching, or proprietary RPC dependency.",
    "The schema-v3 mainnet manifest is unconfigured, so the factory, policy registry, protocol, and future ReserveVault targets all fail closed.",
    "Receipt verification checks revert status, confirmations, canonical block hash, receipt stability, and safe head.",
    "Receipt submissions bind a trusted intent ID and the mined sender, destination, calldata, and value.",
    "Deployment validation binds the one factory receipt, CREATE nonce-one registry and nonce-two protocol, the protocol deploymentFactory getter, mutual cross-getters, all three live bytecode templates, the ReserveVault CREATE2 template, and three exact Sourcify records.",
    "Claim-recipient signatures bind chain 1 and the Nakama Policy Registry EIP-712 domain to claimant, claim, recipient, nonce, and deadline.",
    "EIP-1193 signing payloads reject explicit gas limits above the EIP-7825 cap of 0x1000000.",
    "The canonical root depends only on viem; optional Solana peers load only through explicit legacy read and migration subpaths.",
    "All legacy Solana instruction, transaction, safe-client, broadcast, and MagicBlock write paths throw NAKAMA_LEGACY_WRITE_DISABLED."
  ],
